      <figcaption class="figcaption">Shot from the original website that our client brought to us</figcaption>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="row section">

    <div class="column large-6">
      <h2 class="section__title"><span class="section__number">02.</span> It's tough to let things go</h1>
      <p>My client had a tough time moving away from their design implementation of the marketing website. I decided to complete a round of user testing with the current site to see what improvements could be made. Here are a few key findings that I presented to my client:</p>
    </div>

    <div class="column large-6">
      <ul>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-red">
        Potential investors had trouble finding where and how they could sign up
        </li>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-red">Investors had trouble distinguishing if the website was legitimate or a scam</li>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-red">Users wanted to see potential properties without having to sign in</li>
        <li class="card__list card__list--light-red">Even seasoned investors had trouble understanding some of the language being used</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="row section">
    <div class="column large-6">
      <h2 class="section__title"><span class="section__number">03.</span> Outcomes & Lessons</h1>

      <p>With close collaboration and communication, my team and I were able to meet our deadline in time for our client to have it to showcase with investors at his conference.</p>

      <p>The redesign of the marketing website was able to build trust with visitors as they were able to see platform activity such as nearly funded properties, popular properties, and stories from real people. Additionally, once they were ready to commit, there were clear call to actions for investors and loan seekers.</p>
